  "prompt": "What is the most underrated problem in the life of a musician?",
  "response": "One of the most underrated problems in the life of a musician is the challenge of financial instability. While the stereotypical image of a musician often glamorizes fame and fortune, the reality is that many musicians struggle to maintain a steady income. Income can be unpredictable due to the fluctuating nature of performances, gigs, and teaching opportunities, along with the uncertainties around streaming royalties and album sales. This financial unpredictability can create significant stress, making it difficult for musicians to focus on their creative endeavors and invest in their professional growth. Additionally, musicians often have to juggle multiple roles, such as managing their own marketing, booking, and administrative tasks, which can detract from their time and energy for creating music.",
